'''Jon Gorenc Stanković''' (born 14 January 1996) is a Slovenian [[Association football|football]] [[Defender (association football)|defender]] who plays for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]. He has also played for the [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenian under-21]] team.
==Club career==
===Huddersfield Town=== He made his debut for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in an [[EFL Cup]] tie with [[Shrewsbury Town]] on 9 August 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36949806|title=Shrewsbury 2-1 Huddersfield|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=9 August 2016|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> He made his league debut as a late substitute against [[Rotherham United]] on 27 September 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37414579|title=Huddersfield 2-1 Rotherham|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=27 September 2016|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Huddersfield Town on 19 August 2018 in a 6–1 defeat to [[Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45159602|title=Man City 6-1 Huddersfield: Sergio Aguero hat-trick as champions go top|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=19 August 2018|accessdate=20 August 2018}}</ref>
==International career== He was called up to the senior [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] squad by [[Srečko Katanec]] for a friendly against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in June 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=V reprezentanci tudi Gorenc Stanković|url=http://ekipa24.si/clanek/nogomet/reprezentancni-nogomet/574464eea81ff/v-reprezentanci-tudi-gorenc-stankovic|accessdate=1 September 2016|publisher=ekipa24.si|date=24 May 2016}}</ref>
